# ============================================
# DATABASE CONFIGURATION (Turso)
# ============================================
# 
# Turso is a distributed SQLite database.
# Get your database credentials from: https://turso.tech/
#
# 1. Sign up for a free account at https://turso.tech/
# 2. Create a new database in the Turso dashboard
# 3. Copy the database URL (starts with libsql://)
# 4. Generate an authentication token in the Turso dashboard
# 5. Paste both values below
#
# For local development, you can use a local SQLite file:
# DATABASE_URL=file:./db.sqlite
# DATABASE_TOKEN=  (leave empty for local file-based databases)

DATABASE_URL=libsql://your-database-url
DATABASE_TOKEN=your-database-token

# ============================================
# ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION
# ============================================
#
# NODE_ENV: Set to "development" for local development,
#           "production" for production builds,
#           or "test" for running tests
#
# Options: development | test | production

NODE_ENV=development

# ============================================
# TEST CONFIGURATION
# ============================================
#
# For running tests, NODE_ENV should be set to "test"
# Test databases use in-memory SQLite via LibSQL/Turso local mode
# Each test suite gets a unique database instance for isolation
#
# Test database configuration is handled automatically by test utilities
# See test/utils.ts for database helper functions
#
# When running tests:
# - NODE_ENV=test (should be set when running tests)
# - Tests use in-memory databases via test/utils.ts
# - No manual configuration needed for test environment

# ============================================
# SLACK BOT CONFIGURATION
# ============================================
#
# For sending messages to Slack channels via the Web API
#
# 1. Create a Slack App at https://api.slack.com/apps
# 2. Navigate to OAuth & Permissions
# 3. Add Bot Token Scopes:
#    - chat:write (required)
#    - channels:read (optional, for channel lookups)
# 4. Install app to workspace
# 5. Copy the Bot User OAuth Token (starts with xoxb-)
# 6. Invite the bot to channels you want to send messages to
#
# Get your tokens from: https://api.slack.com/apps

SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-your-bot-token-here
